description: U.S. officials are investigating an apparent leak of two “top secret” documents about Israel. The documents appear to outline American spy agencies’ intelligence on possible Israeli preparations for a retaliatory attack on Iran. NBC News’ Ken Dilanian reports on how the secret documents appeared on a social media message board and whether the leak poses a threat to Israel and its allies.
title: U.S. investigates purported leak of ‘top secret’ documents about Israel

description: 3-year-old Sami Mahmoud Ayad was killed by a humanitarian aid airdrop that fell on Khan Younis in southern Gaza. His grandfather told an NBC News team that the family was having breakfast when parachutes started to appear in the sky.
title: Palestinian boy, 3, killed by humanitarian aid airdrop in Gaza

description: King Charles III was heckled in Australia on Monday by an Indigenous senator who shouted “you’re not my king” as the British monarch spoke to lawmakers.
title: ‘Not my king’: King Charles heckled by indigenous senator in Australia

description: Millions of Cubans were enduring electricity blackouts as the government struggled to restore services. Hurricane Oscar, striking the east as a Category 1 storm, added to the disruption.
title: Power outages plague Cuba as Hurricane Oscar adds to island's woes

description: The Israeli military expanded its offensive in Lebanon overnight, striking bank branches across the country to target Hezbollah's finances in an assault that sparked panic in Beirut and sent civilians fleeing for safety.
title: Israel expands Lebanon assault, striking banks to hit Hezbollah's finances

description: King Charles III was heckled by an Australian senator just moments after he finished a speech at the country’s Parliament House. Indigenous independent senator, Lidia Thorpe, strode up the aisle shouting that she did not accept his sovereignty.
title: Heckler confronts King Charles in Australia
